    explanation: "Thymectomy is most beneficial in selected patients with generalized, early-onset, acetylcholine-receptor-antibody-positive MG that is inadequately controlled medically. IVIG does have a role in myasthenic crisis and perioperative stabilization, so an option stating “no role” is false. Rogers notes equal short-term effectiveness of IVIG and plasma exchange and greatest thymectomy benefit in early-onset AChR-positive disease.",
